cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper deals with game theory and communication protocols, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Game Theory (cs.GT), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper's focus on communication protocols and unreliable channels suggests that cs.DS and cs.SY are likely sub-categories, while the use of game theory and strategies points towards cs.LO and cs.GT. The paper's use of formal methods and synthesis of communication protocols suggests that cs.PL is also a possible sub-category.
